CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 14, 1959, pg. A3, reads: "Premiers Cop Third Place - This rocking, riding and swinging group garnered third-place honors last Friday night at the NAACP Youth Council's talent show, in Westinghouse High School auditorium, because they were right in there and down with the happenings in singing, playing instruments and dancing. These members of the "cool school" are, top row, left to right: Kennard Williams, Vann Harris, Wyatt Ruther, 'Rocky' Nelson, Julius Hopson and George Randolph. Bottom row: Lakie McKeller, Alex Richburgh and Pete Walker. - Harris Photo"
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of members of the Premiers band, standing: Kennard Williams, Ira Vann Harris, Wyatt Ruther, "Rocky" Nelson, Julius Hopson, and George Randolph; kneeling: Lakie McKeller, Alex Richburgh holding Seranola guitar, and Pete Walker, posed in Westinghouse High School
